    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-26T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-26T07:00:00-05:00" n="575"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/640: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-26T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 26, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 26—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>287. I have just learned that over the week end the French Assistant Financial
                    Attaché, Monsieur Felix le Norcy, informed Leith-Ross that he had been attached
                    as economic expert to the French Legation in China. This appointment has not as
                    yet been officially communicated to the British Government, which accounts for
                    the statement in my 282 [<hi rend="italic">283</hi>] June 25, 2 p.m.</p>
                <p>Norcy now plans to leave for Shanghai in early August and Peiping about
                    mid-September. He is considered here an adequate number two in the French
                    Financial Attaché’s office and has had many contacts with the press, in
                    presenting the French financial point of view. He is in no way, however, an
                    outstanding figure and of course has not the prestige of Leith-Ross.</p>
                <p>The French Ambassador has confirmed above but adds no official notification can
                    be made until it is certain the health of French Financial Attaché will permit
                    the absence of his assistant.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
